  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Orthopedic implant contact stress credibility assessment (MRL 3)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for finite-element (FE) contact stress prediction of a total knee arthroplasty (TKA) tibial insert under physiological gait loading. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can predict peak contact stress and contact area to within ±15% of experimental measurements for a Class II orthopedic device at Model Risk Level 3. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors are fully assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels across the board. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification and a documented sensitivity analysis on material stiffness and boundary-condition perturbations are included. Decision: Accepted.",
