        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria — uncertainty characterisation",
        "description": "All influential model inputs (elastic modulus, yield stress, tangent modulus, applied load magnitude, flexion angle) assigned probability distributions based on material testing and experimental measurement uncertainty. Monte Carlo sampling (n = 2000) propagates input uncertainty to QoI. Gradation 3 requires quantified uncertainty on all influential inputs."
      },
      "rationale": "Five influential inputs characterised with probability distributions: E ~ N(945, 47²) MPa; σ_y ~ N(21, 1.05²) MPa; E_t ~ N(120, 12²) MPa; applied load ~ N(800, 40²) N; flexion angle ~ N(30, 1.5²) degrees. Monte Carlo (n = 2000, Latin hypercube sampling) propagates input uncertainty. Total QoI uncertainty budget documented in UQ report UQR-TKA-2024. Gradation 3 achieved."
